summaries.short: Season One Finale. Carlo refers Raquel to Valentina, but an item in the newspaper prompts him to reassess the meaning of his profession.
summaries.full: Season One Finale. With his patients' complaints becoming increasingly monotonous to him, Carlo refers Raquel, with a seemingly banal problem, to Valentina. But one morning he comes across an item in the newspaper that arouses suspicion of her connection and he reassess the meaning of his profession.

summaries.short: Season Two Premiere. Now director of the domestic violence NGO, Carlo sees a patient suffering from increasing aggression from her husband.
summaries.full: Season Two Premiere. In his new role as director of the domestic violence NGO, Carlo sees a patient suffering from increasing aggression from her husband, yet she cannot be persuaded to leave him.

summaries.short: Carlo's patient, an Assistant District Attorney, discusses her latest case fighting a court motion for a sex change.
summaries.full: Carlo's patient, an Assistant District Attorney, discusses her latest case where she is working desperately against a court motion for a sex change. Meanwhile, Carlo meets Renato, who happens to be the petitioner in this case. Carlo also consults a Muslim couple as they grapple with an issue concerning their son who faces prejudice.
